### Describe the bug

Hi,

Under pub/sub for which I am trying to deserialize a message into an Event class which contains a Timestamp.

```
protected void loggerSink(Event<MyDomainClass> event) {
     logger.debug("Received a message of type " + event.getType());
      ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
      List<MyDomainClass>datas = mapper.convertValue(event.getMessage(), new TypeReference<List<MyDomainClass>>() {
      });
}
```
```
@Cacheable
@Entity(name = "ws_xxxx")
public class MyDomainClass extends PanacheEntityBase {
   @Column(name = "updating_date")
   public Timestamp timestamp;
}
```

It's working within PubSub Emulator But one deploy on CloudRun this exception appears:

`WARNING [co.go.cl.pu.v1.MessageDispatcher] (Gax-2) MessageReceiver failed to process ack ID: BCEhPjA-RVNEUAYWLF1GSFE3GQhoUQ5PXiM_NSAoRRABIGwLNEJcdA1oXFx1BlkNEXd4YnBrWkALAk9TVm9D2tHn_2pXJ1UJEXd8Y3BpXBoIA0RWf1tzrpauiPmbzGYXIkq8vfrJbDOu49pgZho9WxJLLD5-PTFFQV5AEkw2BERJUytDCypYEU4, the message will be nacked.: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Failed to find class `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.DateDeserializers$TimestampDeserializer` for handling values of type `java.sql.Timestamp`, problem: (java.lang.ClassNotFoundException) **com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.DateDeserializers$TimestampDeserializer**`

I see an anwser using **@RegisterForReflection**. But I don't know which class i have to set.

Best regards


